The article is a statement made by President Barack Obama on March 17, 2009, regarding the budget. He discusses the progress being made by the budget committees and emphasizes that the budget is not just numbers on a page, but an economic blueprint for the future. Obama highlights the tough choices that have been made to cut the deficit in half by the end of his first term and reduce it by $2 trillion over the next decade. He emphasizes the importance of investments in long-term prosperity, such as health care reform, education, and renewable energy. Obama also mentions that the budget will not raise taxes for families making less than $250,000 a year and encourages constructive alternative solutions from both Democrats and Republicans. He concludes by urging Congress to pass a budget that puts the nation on the road to lasting prosperity.